<codeline lineno="7"><highlight class="comment"><sp/>*<sp/>@section<sp/>Analysis_intro<sp/>Introduction</highlight></codeline>
<codeline lineno="8"><highlight class="comment"><sp/>*<sp/>The<sp/>`Analysis`<sp/>class,<sp/>implemented<sp/>in<sp/>Cython,<sp/>serves<sp/>as<sp/>the<sp/>primary<sp/>entry<sp/>point<sp/>and<sp/>orchestrator<sp/>for<sp/>managing<sp/>and<sp/>executing<sp/>data<sp/>processing<sp/>workflows<sp/>within<sp/>the<sp/>AnalysisG<sp/>framework.<sp/>It<sp/>provides<sp/>a<sp/>comprehensive<sp/>interface<sp/>for<sp/>configuring<sp/>and<sp/>running<sp/>complex<sp/>analyses,<sp/>including<sp/>the<sp/>integration<sp/>of<sp/>samples,<sp/>event<sp/>and<sp/>graph<sp/>templates,<sp/>selection<sp/>criteria,<sp/>metric<sp/>calculations,<sp/>and<sp/>machine<sp/>learning<sp/>models.<sp/>This<sp/>class<sp/>is<sp/>designed<sp/>to<sp/>streamline<sp/>the<sp/>entire<sp/>analysis<sp/>pipeline,<sp/>from<sp/>data<sp/>input<sp/>to<sp/>result<sp/>generation,<sp/>leveraging<sp/>a<sp/>high-performance<sp/>C++<sp/>backend<sp/>for<sp/>critical<sp/>operations.</highlight></codeline>
